cdsctl_part_1:
curl {{apiURL}}/download/cdsctl/{{osChoice}}/{{archChoice}}{{variant}} -o cdsctl

# add execution rights on cdsctl
chmod +x cdsctl

# check if binary is ok, this command will display cdsctl version
./cdsctl version
cdsctl_part_2:
# The cdsctl login command will store credentials in your keychain
./cdsctl login --api-url {{apiURL}} -u {{username}}

# this command will display your username, fullname, email
# if you see them, cdsctl is well configured
./cdsctl user me
cdsctl_part_3:
# The cdsctl shell to browse your projects and workflows without the need to open a browser.
# see https://ovh.github.io/cds/docs/components/cdsctl/shell/
cdsctl shell

# help is available on each cdsctl command
cdsctl --help
cdsctl_part_4:
# Launch a workflow, consider running cdsctl from a directory containing a git repository known from CDS
cdsctl workflow run

# You can explicitly set a projet and workflow
cdsctl workflow run PRJ_KEY WORKFLOW_NAME

# flags --interactive or --open-web-browser may interest you, help for all details
cdsctl workflow run --help
cdsctl_part_5:
# Check status of a run
cdsctl workflow status

# --track command will wait the end of the workflow run
cdsctl workflow status --track
cdsctl_part_6:
# Add a git alias in your gitconfig file
$ cat ~/.gitconfig
[alias]
   track = !cdsctl workflow status --track
cdsctl_part_7:
# Update from current CDS Platform
cdsctl update

# Update from latest release on github
cdsctl update --from-github
cdsctl_part_8:
# All commands have the flag --format. This is useful for use cdsctl in your script
# Formats available: table, json, yaml
cdsctl user list --format json
